{
  "texts": [
    "where H 0 is the Hubble constant, H(z) is the Hubble parameter for which we assume standard ΛCDM cosmology with the Planck-2018 fiducial parameters (Planck Collaboration VI 2020), and t 0 is the cosmic time today.",
    "The sum is over the cusp, kink and kink-kink contributions (labelled with the index b) for which q b = 4/3, 5/3 and 2 respectively.",
    "Our analysis follows the one presented in Leclere et al. (2023), which was based on six pulsars with the best timing precision from the EPTA early Data Release 2 (Chen et al. 2021).",
    "We now analyse the DR2new dataset with 25 pulsars, using the (computationally heavy) hierarchical likelihood data analysis method A94, page 16 of 30 described in Paper III.",
    "We sample the SGWB parameters (Gµ) or (Gµ, N k) as well as the individual pulsar noise parameters."
  ]
}